Also, edited s3_driver.py so it can upload pandas DataFrames.

title: Bayes Prior Distribution Change
body:
#### Summary of changes
**Asana Task:** [Bayes Prior Change](https://app.asana.com/0/1132391493673593/1202553773143369/f)

Right now whenever thresholds are above a certain value we always multiply the variance of the prior distribution by a factor of 10. This change will make it so that we only increase the variance of the prior distribution if we have a decent amount of new data.

title: Mkt requirements
body:
#### Summary of changes
**Asana Task:** [TASK_NAME](TASK_LINK)

My modification of the requirements and readme reflects my difficulty in setting up the environment with a new MacBook M1
1. changed from a specific python version to python3 venv. I am open to using virtualenv if we really want a specific python version. Python 3.7.5 is quite old and a chore to get working with the new MacBooks.2. 

2. limited requirements.txt to mostly direct imports (few transitive dependencies). I encountered issues with installing grpcio, numpy, pandas, psycopg2-binary. There also appear to be many unused packages like google-ads. Limiting these packages will be easier to maintain and upgrade. 

3. Refreshed the readme. I tried to align with the Airflow repo readme. Be more explicit about creating a dedicated virtual environment.

I'm new to this repo, so I intend this to be an open discussion
